Demonstrate the surprising precision loss when converting `long` to `float`:

**Example:**
long big = 1234567890123456789L;
float f = (float) big;
long back = (long) f;
big == back => false! (precision lost in float's 23-bit mantissa)

**Key insight:** `float` has only 7 significant decimal digits; `long` has 19. Large longs lose precision when cast to float.

